snippet.textDisplay:
It's almost 10 years I've been listening to this song.
every single time this song delivers the feeling of pain and silence, it reminds us Abbas, who sacrificed his life for his brother in Karbala, showing bravery and loyalty in the face of injustice. This isn’t just music, it’s a soul offering wrapped in sound.

snippet.textDisplay:
28/12/24 

Today I have decided to make this world by journal.

I feel I find solace discovering songs, listening to them. While I listen to them I realise I have parts missing to feel them, like I dont have wind in a grassland, or I am sitting besides the woods but there is no fire in this cold world. 

I will keep writing, because that way I am able to live and listen.
